cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MED, cs.IR 

This paper presents a machine learning approach for segmenting hyperreflective foci in optical coherence tomography (OCT) images of the retina. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of machine learning models for segmentation also suggests that it could be relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with medical imaging and disease monitoring, which could make it relevant to the medical imaging (cs.MED) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
